In small mixing bowl beat cream cheese on medium speed of electric mixer until fluffy. Add 3 tablespoons sugar and vanilla. Beat until combined. Beat in 1 egg until just combined. Spread in crust. In large bowl combine 2 eggs, pumpkin, 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg. Stir in milk. Place crust on baking sheet. Spoon pumpkin mixture over cream cheese mixture. Bake on baking sheet at 350 degrees F about 55 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack for 1 hour. Refrigerate at least 3 hours. Garnish as desired. Store in refrigerator.